WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.300 --> 00:00:06.140
NICOLAS GARNIER: Hello, hello
everybody, and welcome to

00:00:06.140 --> 00:00:09.070
"What's New with the Google
Drive SDK: One Year Later." My

00:00:09.070 --> 00:00:10.800
name is Nicolas.

00:00:10.800 --> 00:00:12.030
I'm a developer advocate.

00:00:12.030 --> 00:00:16.059
I've been working on Google
Drive pretty much since we

00:00:16.059 --> 00:00:19.000
launched Google Drive
about a year ago.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:22.120
During this session we're going
to have a look at what

00:00:22.120 --> 00:00:26.090
happened to the Google Drive
SDK since we launched it,

00:00:26.090 --> 00:00:28.946
basically, up until today.

00:00:28.946 --> 00:00:32.369
As I said, we launched Google
Drive about a year ago.

00:00:32.369 --> 00:00:34.610
And when we launched Google
Drive, we had

00:00:34.610 --> 00:00:36.120
several goals in mind.

00:00:36.120 --> 00:00:40.650
So of course one of the goals
was to offer to our users a

00:00:40.650 --> 00:00:44.750
way to back up all of the
files that are in their

00:00:44.750 --> 00:00:50.320
desktop and upload it online
and share their files with

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:51.300
their friends, for example.

00:00:51.300 --> 00:00:54.600
So that's pretty much what
people expected from a service

00:00:54.600 --> 00:00:56.500
like Google Drive.

00:00:56.500 --> 00:00:58.350
But that was actually
not the main goal.

00:00:58.350 --> 00:01:02.260
The main goal was really to
make Google Drive a pretty

00:01:02.260 --> 00:01:05.760
central place on the
web platform.

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:07.010
And we'll see that
in just a second.

00:01:09.300 --> 00:01:11.230
You guys all know now
that the web is

00:01:11.230 --> 00:01:12.000
really a platform, right?

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:14.480
You're all using web
apps, for instance.

00:01:14.480 --> 00:01:17.810
I know I have moved online for
a lot of my work needs.

00:01:17.810 --> 00:01:23.830
For example, I use Google
Sheet, Google Docs--

00:01:23.830 --> 00:01:25.210
that's the old name--

00:01:25.210 --> 00:01:27.970
Google Slides, pretty
much everyday now.

00:01:27.970 --> 00:01:30.160
And there's a lot more than
you can do online.

00:01:30.160 --> 00:01:33.720
You can find really nice
image editors online.

00:01:33.720 --> 00:01:36.720
I started using, for example,
a online development

00:01:36.720 --> 00:01:38.940
environment lately.

00:01:38.940 --> 00:01:41.240
You can fax files online.

00:01:41.240 --> 00:01:43.640
You can actually listen
to music online.

00:01:43.640 --> 00:01:48.420
So my point is, there is now a
lot of very high quality web

00:01:48.420 --> 00:01:51.030
apps that you can
find and use.

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:54.570
And we see this trend where
people are really moving away

00:01:54.570 --> 00:01:57.160
from the desktop and really
started doing more and more

00:01:57.160 --> 00:01:59.930
things online.

00:01:59.930 --> 00:02:03.940
As people are really moving
online, they wanted to have a

00:02:03.940 --> 00:02:06.140
place to basically keep all
of their files online.

00:02:06.140 --> 00:02:08.340
And that's why we launched
Google Drive.

00:02:08.340 --> 00:02:14.640
It's really to provide our users
a place to manage and

00:02:14.640 --> 00:02:17.800
organize all of the
files online.

00:02:17.800 --> 00:02:21.810
But not only that, it's really
also a place for your favorite

00:02:21.810 --> 00:02:25.670
web apps to be able to write
files on your Google Drive,

00:02:25.670 --> 00:02:29.830
have a place to write and
read files, basically.

00:02:29.830 --> 00:02:32.150
That's also why we built Google
Drive, is the case.

00:02:32.150 --> 00:02:42.010
It's really to basically
offer the web

00:02:42.010 --> 00:02:44.530
platform a file system.

00:02:44.530 --> 00:02:46.680
So that that's really important
message here.

00:02:46.680 --> 00:02:48.410
Google Drive is really the file

00:02:48.410 --> 00:02:52.130
system for the web platform.

00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:55.650
And the SDK, it's pretty much
the programmatic interface to

00:02:55.650 --> 00:02:56.900
this file system.

00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:04.730
So we really wanted to make the
SDK a really easy to use,

00:03:04.730 --> 00:03:06.790
easy to integrate
user experience.

00:03:06.790 --> 00:03:11.960
So as you'll see, we wanted to
make it pretty much as easy to

00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:16.470
integrate as a desktop
application would today

00:03:16.470 --> 00:03:19.670
integrate with the local
file system.

00:03:19.670 --> 00:03:20.880
We actually didn't want
to stop there.

00:03:20.880 --> 00:03:24.350
We wanted to not only make it
as easy for web applications

00:03:24.350 --> 00:03:29.730
to use this web file system that
Drive SDK is, but we also

00:03:29.730 --> 00:03:34.410
wanted to use some of the
collaboration and security

00:03:34.410 --> 00:03:37.190
features that are available on
the web today to make it

00:03:37.190 --> 00:03:41.280
basically more powerful and more
secure that if your app

00:03:41.280 --> 00:03:42.530
was not on the cloud.

00:03:46.210 --> 00:03:48.930
When we launched Google Drive,
of course, what was available

00:03:48.930 --> 00:03:53.470
is a programmatic way to access
and manage files.

00:03:53.470 --> 00:03:55.730
That's really the API
part of our SDK.

00:03:59.860 --> 00:04:02.960
With the Google API, you can
basically do all of the things

00:04:02.960 --> 00:04:04.730
that you would expect
from a file system.

00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:08.730
You can manage, read,
write file.

00:04:08.730 --> 00:04:09.560
You can delete files.

00:04:09.560 --> 00:04:12.040
You can create files
on Google Drive.

00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:14.400
All that is using a REST API.

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:20.700
It's using also OAuth 2.0 for
our authorization mechanism.

00:04:20.700 --> 00:04:24.100
This is all pretty much expected
from the file system

00:04:24.100 --> 00:04:29.000
from a data web API that
Google could provide.

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:32.450
One thing that's pretty special,
though, is one of the

00:04:32.450 --> 00:04:34.500
security features that we
launched with Google

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:36.980
Drive a year ago.

00:04:36.980 --> 00:04:39.060
There's basically a way for
application to restrict

00:04:39.060 --> 00:04:43.190
themselves to only gain access
to the files they have either

00:04:43.190 --> 00:04:47.740
created or the files that the
user has manually opened

00:04:47.740 --> 00:04:49.060
through the drive
user interface.

00:04:49.060 --> 00:04:52.670
We'll see how that's possible
in just a second.

00:04:52.670 --> 00:04:55.560
And this is actually very, very

00:04:55.560 --> 00:04:56.690
convenient for users, right?

00:04:56.690 --> 00:04:59.180
Because the application doesn't
gain access to the

00:04:59.180 --> 00:05:02.610
entire Google Drive, at least
not programmatically.

00:05:02.610 --> 00:05:06.120
They're not restricted to only
a subfolder, like sometimes

00:05:06.120 --> 00:05:07.720
it's done here.

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:10.430
The user can potentially open
any of the files that is in

00:05:10.430 --> 00:05:15.610
the user's drive with an app,
but without giving the access

00:05:15.610 --> 00:05:22.110
to files that potentially you
wouldn't want to give access

00:05:22.110 --> 00:05:25.390
to applications out there.

00:05:25.390 --> 00:05:28.860
That brings us to the other very
important feature that

00:05:28.860 --> 00:05:31.320
was launched with Google
Drive a year ago.

00:05:31.320 --> 00:05:33.260
It's the ability for the
application to deeply

00:05:33.260 --> 00:05:37.300
integrate with the user
interface, with the user

00:05:37.300 --> 00:05:41.720
interface case of the
Drive file export.

00:05:41.720 --> 00:05:44.790
Basically, how it works is,
apps can register to

00:05:44.790 --> 00:05:47.100
[? append ?] certain
file types.

00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:51.210
For example, a user could go in
his drive and try to open

00:05:51.210 --> 00:05:56.620
that vacation photo that you
see on the screen here with

00:05:56.620 --> 00:05:58.100
PicMonkey or Pixlr Editor.

00:05:58.100 --> 00:06:00.860
If you don't know what PicMonkey
or Pixlr Editor is,

00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:05.610
these are pretty powerful image
editors that are online,

00:06:05.610 --> 00:06:09.140
that you can use online and
that have integrated with

00:06:09.140 --> 00:06:11.860
Google Drive.

00:06:11.860 --> 00:06:21.440
How it works is, the user is
going to connect his Google

00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:23.990
Drive-enabled applications
to Google Drive.

00:06:23.990 --> 00:06:28.180
And how he can do that, he can
basically go to his Drive and

00:06:28.180 --> 00:06:32.940
directly browse all of the
applications that are Google

00:06:32.940 --> 00:06:38.260
Drive compatible that
are available today.

00:06:38.260 --> 00:06:41.880
He will simply go to his Create
Menu, click on Connect

00:06:41.880 --> 00:06:45.410
More Apps, and he will be able
to browse and search all of

00:06:45.410 --> 00:06:48.830
these Google Drive
compatible apps.

00:06:48.830 --> 00:06:53.120
There's apps like AutoCAD,
for example.

00:06:53.120 --> 00:06:54.250
There are music players.

00:06:54.250 --> 00:06:58.720
There are diagramming
applications, photo editors.

00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:00.700
There's a lot you can
do right now.

00:07:00.700 --> 00:07:03.080
And we're going to have
a look at one of them,

00:07:03.080 --> 00:07:03.705
called Hello Fax.

00:07:03.705 --> 00:07:07.690
It allows you to do very
easily fax documents.

00:07:07.690 --> 00:07:11.610
And they've done a pretty good
job on their Google Drive

00:07:11.610 --> 00:07:13.360
integration.

00:07:13.360 --> 00:07:14.580
So this is my drive.

00:07:14.580 --> 00:07:15.890
There's only a few documents.

00:07:15.890 --> 00:07:20.110
And what I want to do is, I
want to fax that PDF here

00:07:20.110 --> 00:07:21.090
that's on my screen.

00:07:21.090 --> 00:07:23.650
So how I'm going to do
that, is I'm going to

00:07:23.650 --> 00:07:28.070
look for Hello Fax.

00:07:28.070 --> 00:07:33.110
I simply have to search the
kind of embedded app store

00:07:33.110 --> 00:07:35.020
that's inside Google
Drive here.

00:07:35.020 --> 00:07:36.820
I'm going to connect
Hello Fax.

00:07:36.820 --> 00:07:38.990
And I get a confirmation
dialog.

00:07:38.990 --> 00:07:42.990
And then I can do as a user
is right-click, Open With,

00:07:42.990 --> 00:07:45.390
select Hello Fax.

00:07:45.390 --> 00:07:48.330
Now Hello Fax is part of the
options to open that the type

00:07:48.330 --> 00:07:49.970
of file, PDF.

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:52.870
This is the first time I'm
running Hello Fax from Drive.

00:07:52.870 --> 00:07:57.530
I get this OAuth 2.0
configuration dialog, just

00:07:57.530 --> 00:08:02.780
basically granting Hello Fax
access to my Google Drive.

00:08:02.780 --> 00:08:04.140
Now I get redirected
to Hello Fax.

00:08:04.140 --> 00:08:05.390
Hello Fax has these
two features.

00:08:05.390 --> 00:08:09.800
One is online signature
management feature.

00:08:09.800 --> 00:08:14.080
The other one is their faxing
feature, which I want to use.

00:08:14.080 --> 00:08:16.320
And as you can see here,
Hello Fax is

00:08:16.320 --> 00:08:18.580
pulling my PDF, basically.

00:08:18.580 --> 00:08:20.470
It's a very simple,
very small PDF.

00:08:20.470 --> 00:08:21.690
It just says Hello.

00:08:21.690 --> 00:08:22.530
And that's it.

00:08:22.530 --> 00:08:23.560
Hello Fax has my PDF.

00:08:23.560 --> 00:08:27.670
I can now use Hello Fax
to fax that PDF.

00:08:27.670 --> 00:08:29.300
I could enter any bogus
phone number.

00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:32.480
It's going to go to
Austria somewhere.

00:08:32.480 --> 00:08:33.190
And that's it.

00:08:33.190 --> 00:08:37.159
Hello Fax is actually trying
to send my PDF to

00:08:37.159 --> 00:08:39.500
this number I entered.

00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:42.230
Hello Fax does a lot more
cool stuff with the

00:08:42.230 --> 00:08:43.530
Google Drive API.

00:08:43.530 --> 00:08:47.980
For example, they will upload
a confirmation fax to your

00:08:47.980 --> 00:08:48.860
Google Drive.

00:08:48.860 --> 00:08:51.710
You can also purchase, for
example, phone numbers and

00:08:51.710 --> 00:08:54.630
receive all of your faxes
through Hello Fax.

00:08:54.630 --> 00:08:58.010
They're going to write all of
those faxes you receive as PDF

00:08:58.010 --> 00:08:59.160
inside Google Drive directly.

00:08:59.160 --> 00:09:01.110
So there's all pretty
nice features.

00:09:04.850 --> 00:09:09.510
When we launched Google Drive
there was 18 partners that

00:09:09.510 --> 00:09:12.510
were offering this Deep
UI integration.

00:09:12.510 --> 00:09:18.530
And I think you're going to
find about 150 apps today

00:09:18.530 --> 00:09:21.920
connectable through
the Google Drive.

00:09:21.920 --> 00:09:24.370
There's of course a lot more
applications using the API on

00:09:24.370 --> 00:09:29.660
Android, on iOS, and on the
web that are not as deeply

00:09:29.660 --> 00:09:32.060
integrated as these 150 apps.

00:09:32.060 --> 00:09:34.260
So you can find a lot more.

00:09:34.260 --> 00:09:35.680
You can find a lot of
cool applications.

00:09:35.680 --> 00:09:39.980
But there's also a lot of room
still left for you to

00:09:39.980 --> 00:09:41.570
basically get noticed
inside Google Drive.

00:09:41.570 --> 00:09:45.430
So if you're interested in
learning more about this, I

00:09:45.430 --> 00:09:49.110
invite you to attend Steven
and Josh's session.

00:09:49.110 --> 00:09:54.450
It's called "Getting Your App
Noticed Inside Google Drive."

00:09:54.450 --> 00:09:57.360
So they're going to talk about
how, of course, you can get

00:09:57.360 --> 00:09:59.810
your app noticed inside Google
Drive, but also how Google

00:09:59.810 --> 00:10:03.310
Drive can be an efficient way
to drive traffic or drive

00:10:03.310 --> 00:10:05.470
users to your application.

00:10:05.470 --> 00:10:09.420
That's at 10:00 AM tomorrow.

00:10:09.420 --> 00:10:13.450
We also wanted to allow you to
very easily integrate with

00:10:13.450 --> 00:10:13.770
Google Drive.

00:10:13.770 --> 00:10:16.850
So we've built basically
a bunch of widgets.

00:10:16.850 --> 00:10:21.140
These widgets are common UI
components that you can

00:10:21.140 --> 00:10:26.780
integrate very easily inside
your web apps, typically using

00:10:26.780 --> 00:10:30.030
a few lines of JavaScript
or a few lines of HTML.

00:10:30.030 --> 00:10:34.080
And the first widget that we
launched, actually, when we

00:10:34.080 --> 00:10:36.690
launched the API that was
available a year ago, is the

00:10:36.690 --> 00:10:37.400
Google Picker.

00:10:37.400 --> 00:10:43.110
So the Google Picker is really
a widget that allows your

00:10:43.110 --> 00:10:47.910
users to basically browse their
file and select files

00:10:47.910 --> 00:10:49.180
inside Google Drive.

00:10:49.180 --> 00:10:52.920
That's basically the equivalent
of, if you were on

00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:55.490
the desktop application,
starting a file explorer

00:10:55.490 --> 00:10:59.060
process to let your users
select a file.

00:10:59.060 --> 00:11:03.100
We basically wanted to bring
the same easy integration

00:11:03.100 --> 00:11:07.740
experience to web applications
online.

00:11:07.740 --> 00:11:10.450
The second widget that was
launched actually at Google

00:11:10.450 --> 00:11:14.650
I/O last year, so a bit less
than a year ago, is the

00:11:14.650 --> 00:11:15.520
Sharing Dialog.

00:11:15.520 --> 00:11:18.270
So it's actually the same exact
sharing dialog that

00:11:18.270 --> 00:11:20.790
you're going to find in web
properties like Google Docs,

00:11:20.790 --> 00:11:25.430
Google Spreadsheets, or Google
Slides, actually even in

00:11:25.430 --> 00:11:26.630
Google Drive.

00:11:26.630 --> 00:11:29.520
It's exactly the same UI, except
you're going to be able

00:11:29.520 --> 00:11:33.270
to use it inside your website,
embedded inside your website,

00:11:33.270 --> 00:11:38.580
and let user share files
directly from your website.

00:11:38.580 --> 00:11:40.490
So if you think about it,
that's actually not

00:11:40.490 --> 00:11:42.170
so trivial to build.

00:11:42.170 --> 00:11:46.070
We have a nice feature like
Autocomplete here.

00:11:46.070 --> 00:11:50.330
The widget is also going to look
at if your Google Apps

00:11:50.330 --> 00:11:53.800
administrator has enabled public
sharing and display

00:11:53.800 --> 00:11:55.540
that option or not.

00:11:55.540 --> 00:11:58.130
It's also going to send an email
to the people you've

00:11:58.130 --> 00:12:01.600
shared the document with
when you confirm.

00:12:01.600 --> 00:12:05.280
So all that is already built for
you and you can integrate

00:12:05.280 --> 00:12:06.580
this very easily inside
your website.

00:12:06.580 --> 00:12:07.950
I think that's a few lines
of JavaScript.

00:12:10.460 --> 00:12:14.170
Also the last widget that we
launched-- that was actually

00:12:14.170 --> 00:12:16.700
last week-- is the Safe
to Drive button.

00:12:16.700 --> 00:12:20.480
So Safe to Drive button is
pretty simple, right?

00:12:20.480 --> 00:12:25.590
It basically allows your users
to download the file directly

00:12:25.590 --> 00:12:28.260
to Google Drive instead of
having to download it locally

00:12:28.260 --> 00:12:30.170
and maybe re-upload it.

00:12:30.170 --> 00:12:33.230
That's all done in basically
one operation.

00:12:33.230 --> 00:12:36.440
And what's really nice about
that widget is that it's only

00:12:36.440 --> 00:12:37.690
really two lines of HTML.

00:12:40.810 --> 00:12:41.730
I'm not kidding.

00:12:41.730 --> 00:12:43.510
You copy and paste those two
lines of HTML and it should

00:12:43.510 --> 00:12:46.290
work pretty much for most of
the files you could think

00:12:46.290 --> 00:12:52.020
about downloading from
your website.

00:12:52.020 --> 00:12:53.560
I'm actually going to
show you some of

00:12:53.560 --> 00:12:55.410
these widgets in action.

00:12:55.410 --> 00:12:58.626
The first app I wanted to show
you is called Neutron Drive.

00:12:58.626 --> 00:13:02.360
Neutron Drive is a nice online
ID for Google Drive.

00:13:02.360 --> 00:13:04.120
It's nice and integrated
with Google Drive.

00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:06.990
Let me switch to
Neutron Drive.

00:13:06.990 --> 00:13:07.740
This is Neutron Drive.

00:13:07.740 --> 00:13:12.680
As you can see, I'm currently
editing an HTML file in there.

00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:17.330
And if I wanted to open a file
that's in my drive, I could

00:13:17.330 --> 00:13:21.300
click this button here and
Neutron Drive just pulls up

00:13:21.300 --> 00:13:23.260
the Google Picker, where
I could simply

00:13:23.260 --> 00:13:24.790
open another file.

00:13:24.790 --> 00:13:29.230
What I could do also is, for
example, share that file,

00:13:29.230 --> 00:13:32.280
right-click on the tab here
and select Sharing.

00:13:32.280 --> 00:13:35.330
You can see that's the
embeddable sharing dialog

00:13:35.330 --> 00:13:36.780
that's inside Neutron Drive.

00:13:36.780 --> 00:13:40.430
I could just share it with my
friends or my colleagues.

00:13:44.060 --> 00:13:48.070
Also the other widget was the
Safe to Drive button.

00:13:48.070 --> 00:13:51.480
O'Reilly was one of the launch
partners for that button, so

00:13:51.480 --> 00:13:54.800
they had integrated the
button at launch.

00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:56.360
That was just a week ago.

00:13:56.360 --> 00:13:59.600
And as you can see here, that's
actually one of their

00:13:59.600 --> 00:14:02.000
free e-books that you
can download.

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:04.790
And they've added a bunch of
buttons, one for each of the

00:14:04.790 --> 00:14:07.840
file formats that you
can download.

00:14:07.840 --> 00:14:11.080
Here I'm simply going
to download the PDF.

00:14:11.080 --> 00:14:12.650
You have to confirm.

00:14:12.650 --> 00:14:15.510
As you can see, the PDF
is downloading.

00:14:15.510 --> 00:14:17.460
It's actually a pretty
