00:26:13.740 --> 00:26:18.290
One of the next features that
is coming up is called Push

00:26:18.290 --> 00:26:18.860
Notifications.

00:26:18.860 --> 00:26:23.300
So hopefully, this is coming
very, very soon.

00:26:23.300 --> 00:26:24.680
I'm saying that because
I think we also

00:26:24.680 --> 00:26:27.080
announced it last year.

00:26:27.080 --> 00:26:29.580
So hopefully, this will be
available very, very soon.

00:26:29.580 --> 00:26:33.710
Push Notification is really a
way for your application to

00:26:33.710 --> 00:26:36.100
get notified when something
changes in the

00:26:36.100 --> 00:26:38.790
user's Google Drive.

00:26:38.790 --> 00:26:41.900
For example, when the user
modifies a file or adds a new

00:26:41.900 --> 00:26:45.260
file or deletes a file in his
drive, you could potentially

00:26:45.260 --> 00:26:48.470
be notified by a server
to server call.

00:26:48.470 --> 00:26:53.310
So that really solves some
of the issues where--

00:26:53.310 --> 00:26:55.430
basically if your application
wanted to know if something

00:26:55.430 --> 00:26:57.870
has changed in the user's drive,
they would have to

00:26:57.870 --> 00:27:00.070
check, basically poll every five
minutes, let's say, or

00:27:00.070 --> 00:27:02.400
every half an hour, or
every day, to see if

00:27:02.400 --> 00:27:03.620
something has changed.

00:27:03.620 --> 00:27:05.550
Well, now you won't have to
do that anymore with Push

00:27:05.550 --> 00:27:06.090
Notifications.

00:27:06.090 --> 00:27:10.010
You will, basically, almost in
real time get notified when

00:27:10.010 --> 00:27:12.550
something has changed
in the user's drive.

00:27:12.550 --> 00:27:18.210
And potentially, then, get
faster notification, take

00:27:18.210 --> 00:27:19.380
faster action.

00:27:19.380 --> 00:27:21.750
And it's a win-win, because
for us, you also put less

00:27:21.750 --> 00:27:23.630
strain, probably,
on our servers.

00:27:23.630 --> 00:27:26.380
Instead of polling every five
minutes or every 30 minutes,

00:27:26.380 --> 00:27:30.250
you'll just have to wait until
a notification arrives.

